WEBVTT

00:01.910 --> 00:03.393
I feel bad saying this,
I do,

00:03.395 --> 00:05.729
but Coleen's makeup,
it just -- it looks terrible.

00:05.731 --> 00:06.897
Oh, my God!

00:06.899 --> 00:08.232
I think so, too!

00:08.234 --> 00:10.325
And when is the last time
she put on blue eye shadow?

00:10.327 --> 00:12.069
I don't know.
Our prom, maybe?

00:12.071 --> 00:13.828
Well, I wouldn't know.
I wasn't asked to prom.

00:13.830 --> 00:14.996
It's been 22 years.

00:14.998 --> 00:16.240
I think we gotta
let this one go.

00:16.242 --> 00:17.516
I'm trying.
Guys...

00:17.518 --> 00:18.458
There you are.

00:18.460 --> 00:20.552
Coleen's hair is
next-level bad.

00:20.554 --> 00:23.022
I haven't seen her wear it
like this since our prom.

00:23.024 --> 00:24.431
I --
Jodie, you're gonna have
to get over it.

00:24.433 --> 00:26.174
She's trying.
I think we should
say something.

00:26.176 --> 00:28.027
There are girls from high school
out there.

00:28.029 --> 00:31.530
Col's gotta look hot...
so they'll be mad.

00:31.532 --> 00:35.092
Amy: I think I made
her eye shadow worse,

00:35.094 --> 00:36.976
if that's possible.

00:37.129 --> 00:40.205
[ Piano plays somber music ]

00:40.207 --> 00:42.282
Jodie: I can't believe
she's gone.

00:42.284 --> 00:44.101
She made everything
better.

00:44.103 --> 00:46.119
What are we gonna do
without her?

00:46.121 --> 00:48.213
You know, of the four of us,
I really --

00:48.215 --> 00:51.366
I really did think
you'd be the first to go, Amy.

00:51.368 --> 00:54.536
You know, with all the --
the artificial sweeteners

00:54.538 --> 00:58.223
and smoking all those years,
the drinking, the pills,

00:58.225 --> 01:00.542
the gluten,
the jaywalking.

01:00.544 --> 01:04.354
I'm so sorry.
I promise, I will be next.

01:06.141 --> 01:08.901
Coleen would
really like that.

01:08.903 --> 01:10.885
[Squeaks]

01:10.887 --> 01:13.388
♪♪

01:13.390 --> 01:15.482
[<i> Music plays faintly</i> ]

01:15.484 --> 01:17.409
Metallic bronze eye shadow,
hair loose and messy,

01:17.411 --> 01:19.244
light denim jumpsuit,
unless it's winter --

01:19.246 --> 01:20.637
I am rethinking
the jumpsuit.

01:20.639 --> 01:22.989
I think it's a little too causal
for a coffin.

01:22.991 --> 01:24.474
Well, this is going in
the will for now.

01:24.476 --> 01:27.160
You're the greatest husband,
Henry.

01:27.162 --> 01:28.403
Dan will end up just...

01:28.405 --> 01:32.073
pouring me in a jar
with his mother.

01:32.075 --> 01:33.150
Alright.
I gotta get to work.

01:33.152 --> 01:35.094
Okay.
Uh, you gonna be okay?

01:35.096 --> 01:37.596
Yeah.
Maybe in about five years.

01:37.598 --> 01:39.598
It's gonna be okay.

01:39.600 --> 01:40.824
I love you.

01:40.826 --> 01:42.083
Bye, Jodie.

01:42.085 --> 01:44.103
[ Sixpence None The Richer's
"Kiss Me" plays ]

01:44.105 --> 01:47.272
Hey, this is our prom s--

01:47.274 --> 01:49.850
Everyone missed you.
Don't think that they didn't.

01:49.852 --> 01:51.184
You're very missed.

01:51.186 --> 01:52.519
Sorry, that was
the hospital again.

01:52.521 --> 01:54.279
Can't even day drink
at my best friend's funeral

01:54.281 --> 01:56.006
without getting
interrupted.

01:56.008 --> 01:57.932
You didn't talk about the
baby's hair without me, did you?

01:57.934 --> 01:59.267
Oh, it was as bad
as Coleen's.

01:59.269 --> 02:00.435
Coleen never would
have let someone

02:00.437 --> 02:01.787
use hairspray
on her toddler.

02:01.789 --> 02:03.196
She was
the best mother.

02:03.198 --> 02:05.031
She spent every waking moment
with that kid.

02:05.033 --> 02:06.941
It was like,
where Coleen ended,

02:06.943 --> 02:07.868
Lila began.

02:07.870 --> 02:10.036
Okay.
I get it.

02:10.038 --> 02:11.779
You guys think
I'm a terrible mother.

02:11.781 --> 02:12.631
No.

02:12.633 --> 02:13.799
I work long hours.

02:13.801 --> 02:15.542
I can't be home.

02:15.544 --> 02:17.136
You produce
a morning cooking show.

02:17.138 --> 02:18.879
You get off at 1:00
every day.

02:18.881 --> 02:20.455
Yeah, that is true,

02:20.457 --> 02:22.382
but it is a very
high-stress job, okay?

02:22.384 --> 02:25.051
And I need time to decompress
before I go home,

02:25.053 --> 02:27.037
before they go to bed.

02:27.039 --> 02:28.388
I want to be with my kids.
I do.

02:28.390 --> 02:30.149
I love my kids.
I just --

02:30.151 --> 02:32.058
I inherited
the maternal instincts

02:32.060 --> 02:33.968
of a corn chip.

02:33.970 --> 02:35.545
You know what,
and if I didn't know

02:35.547 --> 02:40.141
that she was in Florida
at a different bar right now,

02:40.143 --> 02:43.311
Well, now you're insulting
corn chips.

02:43.313 --> 02:46.390
Someday, I am gonna go home,
and I am gonna be a mother.

02:46.392 --> 02:48.333
Amy, if Coleen's death
has taught us anything,

02:48.335 --> 02:51.578
it's that we don't know
how much time we have left.

02:51.580 --> 02:53.488
And have a hair
and makeup plan in place.

02:53.490 --> 02:55.323
Oh, Amy does.
It's almost in her will.

02:55.325 --> 02:56.750
You know,
'cause I'm next.

02:56.752 --> 02:57.992
Seriously.
It's okay.

02:57.994 --> 02:59.494
Someday is now.

02:59.496 --> 03:02.497
We have to live
our best lives now.

03:03.425 --> 03:06.167
Which is why
I am getting back in shape

03:06.169 --> 03:08.169
and seeing a trainer.

03:08.171 --> 03:11.264
I-I pay in cash so that
Dan doesn't know.

03:11.266 --> 03:13.767
You know the only weight
you have to lose is Dan.

03:13.769 --> 03:15.769
[ Cellphone rings ]

03:15.771 --> 03:17.029
Damn it.

03:17.031 --> 03:18.864
It's work.
I'm not even on call today.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.274
I hate my life.

03:21.276 --> 03:23.927
Somebody better be lying
in a pool of blood.

03:23.929 --> 03:25.779
Oh, good.
Good.

03:25.781 --> 03:27.597
She's a doctor.

03:27.599 --> 03:29.616
♪♪

03:29.618 --> 03:31.526
♪ Hey! ♪

03:31.528 --> 03:33.453
♪♪

03:33.455 --> 03:35.956
-[ Applause ]
-[ Bell rings ]

03:35.958 --> 03:38.050
Sarah, guess what.

03:38.052 --> 03:41.536
I am going straight home
from work today.

03:41.538 --> 03:42.446
Okay?

03:42.448 --> 03:43.555
<i> I was thinking</i>
<i> of Coleen.</i>

03:43.557 --> 03:46.616
And the whole "someday is now"
of it all,

03:46.618 --> 03:51.121
and I have a chance
that she didn't have.

03:51.123 --> 03:55.125
So, I'm gonna be
a really good mom.

03:55.127 --> 03:56.735
In the afternoons.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.553
<i> Scary, huh?</i>
Wow.

03:58.555 --> 04:00.739
I mean, I thought
I had big news.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.056
I just quit medicine.

04:02.058 --> 04:03.316
Yours is way better
than mine.

04:03.318 --> 04:06.078
What do you mean
you quit medicine?

04:06.080 --> 04:07.395
<i> I was in the ER</i>
<i> this morning</i>

04:07.397 --> 04:09.564
<i> at the end</i>
<i> of an 18-hour shift,</i>

04:09.566 --> 04:11.399
<i> and all I could think about</i>
<i> was the burrito that</i>

04:11.401 --> 04:13.901
<i> I left in the doctors lounge</i>
<i> in the microwave.</i>

04:13.903 --> 04:15.087
Ooh, what kind?

04:15.089 --> 04:17.071
<i> Egg white, avocado,</i>
<i> vegan cheese.</i>

04:17.073 --> 04:18.423
<i> You'd hate it.</i>

04:18.425 --> 04:20.259
Anyway, I get back to
the microwave after my surgery,

04:20.261 --> 04:22.427
and someone has eaten half
of my burrito

04:22.429 --> 04:24.170
and just left
the other half just --

04:24.172 --> 04:26.932
just sitting there,
like an animal.

04:26.934 --> 04:27.991
And that was
my breaking point.

04:27.993 --> 04:29.175
I-I-I couldn't
do it anymore.

04:29.177 --> 04:30.660
I-I grabbed my stuff,
and I peaced out.

04:30.662 --> 04:32.771
You couldn't have just bought
another burrito?

04:32.773 --> 04:35.015
It wasn't about the burrito,
Amy.

04:35.017 --> 04:36.166
It was about everything

04:36.168 --> 04:37.501
that I've given up
for medicine --

04:37.503 --> 04:40.428
my -- my -- my 20s, my 30s,
my marriage.

04:40.430 --> 04:42.948
You know that my absence
drove Diana

04:42.950 --> 04:44.432
into the arms
of her acupuncturist.

04:44.434 --> 04:46.026
Well,
I think she drove herself.

04:46.028 --> 04:47.769
It did -- No, it did.
It drove her.

04:47.771 --> 04:49.270
<i> This is why I told you</i>

04:49.272 --> 04:50.605
<i> not to give all your money</i>
<i> to Diana in the divorce,</i>

04:50.607 --> 04:52.457
<i> because what if you had</i>
<i> a psychotic break,</i>

04:52.459 --> 04:54.184
<i> which is what</i>
<i> you're having right now.</i>

04:54.186 --> 04:56.019
I have never
been better.

04:56.021 --> 04:58.021
I am going to
get another job.

04:58.023 --> 04:59.205
A fun one.

04:59.207 --> 05:02.042
<i> You can't.</i>
<i> You are a doctor.</i>

05:02.044 --> 05:06.046
♪ I'm coming ♪

05:06.048 --> 05:08.473
♪ Out ♪

05:08.475 --> 05:09.199
Not anymore.

05:09.201 --> 05:10.958
♪ I'm coming ♪

05:10.960 --> 05:13.127
♪ I'm coming out ♪

05:13.129 --> 05:15.981
♪ I want the world to know ♪

05:15.983 --> 05:19.726
♪ Got to let it show ♪

05:19.728 --> 05:21.987
♪ I'm coming out ♪

05:21.989 --> 05:24.305
♪ I want the world to know ♪

05:24.307 --> 05:26.024
♪ Got to let it show ♪

05:26.026 --> 05:28.735
♪ Got to let it show ♪

05:28.737 --> 05:30.996
♪ I'm ♪

05:30.998 --> 05:33.999
♪ I'm coming out ♪

05:34.001 --> 05:35.149
[ Jodie Groans ]

05:35.151 --> 05:37.227
You're so tight.

05:37.229 --> 05:39.062
Am I hurting you?

05:39.064 --> 05:41.731
It's good.

05:41.733 --> 05:43.583
I like it.

05:43.585 --> 05:46.086
Alright.
Let's go slow.

05:46.088 --> 05:48.996
Hey,
did you lose weight?

05:48.998 --> 05:50.407
2 1/4 pounds.

05:50.409 --> 05:52.184
I'm doing intermittent fasting,
like you said.

05:52.186 --> 05:54.427
And now with the high-intensity
interval training,

05:54.429 --> 05:56.262
you're gonna be building
some lean muscle mass.

05:56.264 --> 05:57.597
I'm telling you,
you're gonna be back

05:57.599 --> 05:59.173
in your skinny jeans
before you know it.

05:59.175 --> 06:01.693
You -- You're gonna look
so freaking hot.

06:01.695 --> 06:04.011
[ Chuckles ]

06:04.013 --> 06:05.346
I'm already in them.

06:05.348 --> 06:07.032
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, my God.

06:07.034 --> 06:09.943
Well, when you get home,
you gotta send me a picture.

06:09.945 --> 06:12.762
Today?

06:12.764 --> 06:13.855
Not in a couple weeks?

06:13.857 --> 06:15.022
You're funny.

06:15.024 --> 06:16.282
Meet me over
by the mini trampoline.

06:16.284 --> 06:17.859
I'm gonna grab you
some water.

06:17.861 --> 06:19.360
Nobody gets me water
at home.

06:19.362 --> 06:21.863
I find that
very hard to believe.

06:21.865 --> 06:27.219
♪♪

06:27.221 --> 06:32.682
♪♪

06:33.727 --> 06:36.103
[ Sighing ] Okay.

06:37.881 --> 06:39.122
Oh, that's a lot.

06:39.124 --> 06:40.565
Mm, mnm-mnm.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.142
[ Tires squeal ]

06:42.144 --> 06:45.904
Maybe someday is tomorrow.

06:45.906 --> 06:47.739
♪♪

06:47.741 --> 06:49.591
[ Cellphone rings ]

06:49.593 --> 06:50.409
Uh, hi.

06:50.411 --> 06:52.059
How's it going
with the kids?

06:52.061 --> 06:53.895
Or did you change your mind
about going home

06:53.897 --> 06:55.805
and you're headed
to Mexico?

06:55.807 --> 06:57.231
[ Tires screech ]

06:57.233 --> 06:58.324
Nope.

06:58.326 --> 07:00.234
I'm almost there.
I'm almost home, yeah.

07:00.236 --> 07:01.569
What,
are you checking up on me?

07:01.571 --> 07:05.482
You didn't think I was actually
gonna go home, or --

07:05.484 --> 07:06.240
No.

07:06.242 --> 07:07.259
Can't a guy
call his wife

07:07.261 --> 07:09.243
and ask if she's run
off to Mexico?

07:09.245 --> 07:10.503
Yeah.
No, you sure can.

07:10.505 --> 07:13.765
But we are --
I am -- is all good.

07:13.767 --> 07:17.827
I am ready to mother.

07:17.829 --> 07:19.179
[ Clang ]
Aaah!

07:19.181 --> 07:21.181
What the hell happened?

07:21.183 --> 07:23.183
I'm -- I'm home.

07:23.185 --> 07:25.502
Hi -- Hi, Luke.

07:25.504 --> 07:27.929
[<i> Upbeat music plays</i> ]
[ Door opens, closes ]

07:27.931 --> 07:30.431
Mommy's home
in the daytime!

07:30.433 --> 07:31.891
Are you not
feeling well?

07:31.893 --> 07:33.026
What? No.
I'm good.

07:33.028 --> 07:35.620
I just wanted to see
my children, so --

07:35.622 --> 07:36.863
Hi, Jules.

07:36.865 --> 07:38.898
Hi! Oh, yes.

07:38.900 --> 07:40.200
See? Okay.
This is great.

07:40.202 --> 07:41.960
Gloria, you can --
you can take off.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.295
I'll -- I'll pay you,
of course.

07:43.297 --> 07:44.796
You never come home
before I have the kids

07:44.798 --> 07:46.189
bathed, fed, and in bed.

07:46.191 --> 07:48.967
Well, I wouldn't --
I wouldn't say never.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.117
Look, my friend died,

07:50.119 --> 07:52.696
and I want to be a good mom,
so...

07:52.698 --> 07:53.863
You don't want me?

07:53.865 --> 07:55.381
I'll go.

07:55.383 --> 07:56.883
Gaga.

07:56.885 --> 07:58.626
Gaga's gotta go.

07:58.628 --> 07:59.886
Gaga's gotta go.

07:59.888 --> 08:01.521
Oh, bye-bye,
my sweet girl.

08:04.042 --> 08:06.634
Oh, don't forget to --

08:06.636 --> 08:07.894
Never mind.

08:07.896 --> 08:09.546
You know
what you're doing.

08:09.548 --> 08:10.304
You're their mother.

08:10.306 --> 08:12.215
I don't want
to insult you.

08:12.217 --> 08:13.158
No, you can insult me!

08:13.160 --> 08:15.827
Gloria!
[ Door closes ]

08:15.829 --> 08:17.829
[<i> Music continues</i> ]

08:17.831 --> 08:19.331
Gaga!

08:19.333 --> 08:21.558
Luke: You're just in time
to play dinosaurs.

08:21.560 --> 08:26.487
You can be a triceratops,
named for its three-horned face.

08:26.489 --> 08:28.915
Don't touch those screens.
Alright.

08:28.917 --> 08:30.324
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:30.326 --> 08:31.843
I'll be in my room!
Don't come in!

08:31.845 --> 08:32.994
Mom, I'm hungry!

08:32.996 --> 08:34.087
There's food
on the floor!

08:34.089 --> 08:35.680
Oh, hey, Andy,
you look pretty!

08:35.682 --> 08:37.073
Don't come in my room!

08:37.075 --> 08:38.408
My mom.
No, you can't meet my mom.

08:38.410 --> 08:41.502
It's not even legal
that we're dating.

08:41.504 --> 08:47.917
♪♪

08:47.919 --> 08:54.607
♪♪

08:54.609 --> 08:55.867
[ Grunts ]

08:55.869 --> 08:57.536
♪♪

08:57.538 --> 08:59.095
Come on!
Come on!

08:59.097 --> 09:00.813
Please. Please.

09:00.815 --> 09:03.250
No. No.

09:04.027 --> 09:05.785
Just fit!

09:05.787 --> 09:07.528
Fit! I'm begging you!

09:07.530 --> 09:08.621
Whoop!

09:08.623 --> 09:11.775
I begged you!

09:11.777 --> 09:13.051
[ Groaning ]

09:13.053 --> 09:16.629
Please, please, please,
please, please, please.

09:16.631 --> 09:18.782
♪♪

09:18.784 --> 09:19.891
So close.

09:19.893 --> 09:21.042
[ Sighs ]

09:21.044 --> 09:23.136
[ Squeaks ]

09:23.138 --> 09:26.956
[ Both growling ]

09:26.958 --> 09:28.382
Okay, this dinosaur's

09:28.384 --> 09:30.960
just gonna catch
its dinosaur breath.

09:30.962 --> 09:32.796
[ Telephone rings ]

09:32.798 --> 09:34.573
Hey.

09:34.575 --> 09:36.223
I-I came home...

09:36.225 --> 09:38.426
to be a good mother
because someday is today.

09:38.428 --> 09:39.485
Something bad's happened.
I need help.

09:39.487 --> 09:41.062
<i> Get over here.</i>
Oh, thank God.

09:41.064 --> 09:42.155
We'll be right over.

09:42.157 --> 09:44.157
Okay! Change of plans.

09:44.159 --> 09:46.008
Field trip.
Okay.

09:46.010 --> 09:47.160
Yep, bring the sticks.
Okay.

09:47.162 --> 09:48.645
I'll bring drums.

09:48.647 --> 09:50.422
Oh, great. Great idea.
That will be fun in the car.

09:50.424 --> 09:53.675
I still have to make Dan
a chicken.

09:56.671 --> 10:01.099
Mom, did you know Florida has
the most shark-infested waters?

10:01.101 --> 10:03.827
Luke, I did not
know that.

10:03.829 --> 10:05.161
[ Chuckles ] Huh.

10:05.163 --> 10:07.254
This is going --
This is going well, right?

10:07.256 --> 10:09.791
You guys are --
Everyone's having a good time.

10:09.793 --> 10:11.517
We're having fun, right?

10:11.519 --> 10:13.427
[ Farts ]

10:13.429 --> 10:15.338
She crapped herself,
and she's sitting on it.

10:15.340 --> 10:18.007
Oh, that is --
Yeah -- [ Gags ]

10:18.009 --> 10:20.267
That is crap.

10:20.269 --> 10:21.527
Oh, she wants Gloria.

10:21.529 --> 10:23.437
Okay, well, Gloria's not here.
It's just Mommy.

10:23.439 --> 10:25.365
Well, it's not --
it's not just Mommy,

10:25.367 --> 10:27.350
but you know what I mean.
Please!

10:27.352 --> 10:29.035
Luke, I'm gonna want you
to hold your breath right now.

10:29.037 --> 10:30.128
It's not healthy.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.963
[ Inhales sharply ]

10:31.965 --> 10:34.799
[ Crying ]

10:34.801 --> 10:36.301
♪♪

10:36.303 --> 10:38.303
Ooh.
Luke: Mom, did you know
peregrine falcons

10:38.305 --> 10:40.972
feed on loons,
pigeons, and ducks?

10:40.974 --> 10:42.365
Great.

10:42.367 --> 10:44.367
That is such good information
right now.

10:44.369 --> 10:46.961
Hi. Thank you so much
for letting us cut.

10:46.963 --> 10:48.796
What?
Okay, it'll be a second.

10:48.798 --> 10:50.206
Oh, my God.

10:50.208 --> 10:52.800
Where are the diapers.
I didn't bring any diapers?

10:52.802 --> 10:55.136
Oh, God!

10:55.138 --> 10:59.215
Are there any emergencies
or 72-hour shifts?

10:59.217 --> 11:00.358
I'm looking for something

11:00.360 --> 11:02.160
where there's no illness
or death,

11:02.162 --> 11:04.220
and I don't have to deliver
bad news to anyone.

11:04.222 --> 11:05.664
I mean,
I'm not gonna sugarcoat it.

11:05.666 --> 11:07.499
Sometimes you have
to tell the customers

11:07.501 --> 11:09.984
that we're out
of the port wine cheddar.

11:09.986 --> 11:12.671
It just happens.

11:12.673 --> 11:15.581
You know, so...

11:15.583 --> 11:16.824
Great.

11:16.826 --> 11:17.992
I'll do it.

11:17.994 --> 11:19.903
Yes.

11:19.905 --> 11:21.054
I haven't interviewed you
yet.

11:21.056 --> 11:22.997
Right.
What would you like to know?

11:22.999 --> 11:26.184
